<paragraph blockId="24.[192,1440,195,284]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[240,590,195,219]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis and discussion.</emphasis>
A bright tawny and completely unmarked species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Austin and Mielke" authorityYear="2008" box="[1202,1366,195,219]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidus">
<emphasis box="[1202,1366,195,219]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">P. splendidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the largest of the known 
<taxonomicName box="[535,716,227,251]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Porphyrogenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[535,716,227,251]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Porphyrogenes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, comparable in size to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moschler" authorityYear="1877" box="[1003,1121,227,251]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Telegonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="probus">
<emphasis box="[1003,1121,227,251]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">P. probus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It appears unique in the genus by having asymmetrical valvae. It resembles the species to be described next (see discussion there).
</paragraph>
